fields.physical_description:
1. cash register; metal upright shape enamelled red with a silver grey cash drawer covered with a panel enamelled cream and a clear plastic covered window at the top. There are 13 keys covered with red, blue, green or cream plastic tops each showing a different monetary amount in old coinage values. When one of the keys is depressed, its value is shown on a raised tongue in the window, a bell rings and the cash drawer opens. The drawer has 4 semi-circular compartments at the
front and two large flat ones at the back with sprung metal tongues (to hold notes). Ht. 7½in x w 6½in x d 7in. 
2,3. £1 notes; paper printed in blue to show the value and BANK OF PLAYTOWN LONDON; 7B5A4370; signed C A SHIER 
4,5. 10/- notes; 10 shillings; paper printed in green to show the value and BANK OF PLAYTOWN LONDON; 7B5A4370; signed C A SHIER. 
*5 - note is torn 
6. £1 note; paper printed in green to show BANK OF KIDDYCASH
TOYTOWN; N04 B12345 
7. 10/- note; cream paper printed in brown to show BANK OF KIDDYCASH TOYTOWN AB3 F9876 
8-10. coins; thin light silver metal; probably a zinc alloy; marked FOR PLAY PURPOSES ONLY. 
     8 - 2/6; 9 - 2/-; 10 - 6d. 
11. coin; brown plastic; KIDDY CASH 1d. 
12-14. coins; silver plastic; KIDDY CASH. 
     12 - 2/6; 13 - 2/-; 14 - 1/-. 
*Kiddy Cash coin are not a true representation of size and are much smaller than the real coins. 
15-29. coins; brown plastic; 1d. TOKEN ONE PENNY 
30-32. coins; brown plastic; ½d. TOKEN HALF PENNY 
33,34. coins; brown plastic; ¼d. TOKEN FARTHING
35-39. coins; gold plastic; 3d. TOKEN THREE PENCE 
40-46. coins; silver plastic; 6d. TOKEN SIX PENCE 
47-55. coins; silver plastic; 1/- TOKEN ONE SHILLING 
56-60. coins; silver plastic; 2/- TOKEN TWO SHILLINGS 
61-63. coins; silver plastic; 2/6 TOKEN HALF CROWN 
64. original box; corrugated cardboard with black printing on all sides and the top flaps. On the sides is a drawing of the cash register and CASH REGISTER AUTOMATICALLY REGISTERS RINGS AND RELEASES TILL/WITH PLAY MONEY/MADE IN ENGLAND. On the top outer flaps is AUTOMATIC CASH REGISTER MADE IN ENGLAND; on the inner flaps are some instructions PRESS KEYS RIGHT DOWN AND KEEP HANDS CLEAR OF THE TILL.
fields.dimensions: Height: 19.68 cm, Width: 17.8 cm, Depth: 20.32 cm
fields.materials_techniques: Metal with plastic and paper play money
fields.location: Museum of Childhood, Homes Gallery, case 4
fields.marks: St. Michael Regd on the cash drawer; printed in gold and cream on a red panel together with MADE IN ENGLAND
fields.history_note: Given to the donor, Patti Kennedy, for her fifth birthday in 1950.
fields.production_note:
Made by: probably made by Chad Valley Co Ltd for Marks & Spencer Ltd and bearing the trade name ST MICHAEL Regd.
England
